    "key_insights": [
      "Clean microservices architecture with Dubbo RPC: The project follows a well-structured consumer-provider pattern using Apache Dubbo for service communication, with clear separation between API contracts and implementations.",
      "Centralized authentication flow: Gateway → AuthServer → AccountManagement chain handles JWT validation and permission checking, creating a proper authentication gateway pattern.",
      "Shared utils module provides cross-cutting concerns: Security (RequireRole/RequirePermission annotations, PermissionCheckAspect), context management (UserInfoManager), and common utilities are properly extracted into a reusable module.",
      "Consistent BFF (Backend-for-Frontend) pattern: Each domain service has consumer (BFF) and provider layers, with consumers handling HTTP requests and providers implementing business logic via Dubbo services.",
      "Potential circular dependency risk: auth-provider depends on account-management for permissions, while account-management may need auth services - should be monitored and kept unidirectional.",
      "Well-designed security infrastructure: Multi-layer security with Gateway JWT filter, method-level permission annotations (@RequireRole, @RequirePermission), and AOP-based permission checking aspect.",
      "Consistent tracing implementation: TraceIdFilter is implemented across all services (auth-provider, auth-consumer, account-provider, third-party-provider, gateway) enabling distributed tracing via MDC.",
      "Database schema organization needs attention: SQL scripts are scattered across multiple provider modules - consider centralizing migration scripts or using a proper migration tool like Flyway/Liquibase.",
      "Third-party service abstraction: External services (OSS, SMS, Email) are properly abstracted behind Dubbo interfaces, allowing for easy mocking and provider switching.",
      "Rate limiting implemented for SMS: SMSRateLimiter in message-system-provider shows proper concern for abuse prevention, should be extended to other sensitive APIs.",
      "Sensitive data handling: SensitiveDataEncryptHandler provides encryption at the MyBatis type handler level for Account, Doctor, and Patient entities.",
      "Missing circuit breaker patterns: While Sentinel is configured at gateway level, individual Dubbo service calls should implement circuit breaker patterns for resilience."
    ]
